Course is designed for students who have previously studied Russian and reached the level A2.

The topics of the course:

My relatives and my friends,
My biography: what year, month, day,
Character and appearance,
Moving around the town,
I like to travel.

The course covers following grammatical areas: verb aspect, numerals, verbs of motion and their prefixes, adverbs of place, all cases in singular and plural.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at enlarging and enhancing the knowledge and skills acquired at the previous level. The course covers the listening, reading and translating of texts, conversations, discussions and work with vocabulary and grammar structures for coping with various communication situations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course a student should be able to:

- use the acquired vocabulary and grammar structures in everyday situations in dialogues and monologues;
- make social contact using advanced vocabulary and expressions;
- describe someone's appearance, make a compliment, explain the way etc.;
- express an opinion on familiar topics;
- understand and use normal language in communication situations on the covered topics;
- write short stories.
